WEBVTT

00:00:00.080 --> 00:00:19.310
And it was so sickening what I was watching happening. But the Lord said, "This is closer than you realize."And then you get to step two, Andrew, which is: "I'd like my child to be really smart."Step three: "I'd like my child to be really tall."And before you know it, we're well on the way to what could be described as eugenics or playing God.

00:00:19.311 --> 00:00:25.544
And they grew the baby to what you had specifically wanted—hair color, eye color.

00:00:25.545 --> 00:00:29.358
You know, like you go to the mall and Build-a-Bear; it was build-a-baby.

00:00:29.359 --> 00:00:36.398
And they could have the gender they wanted, the hair color, the structure of the body; everything was in design.

00:00:36.399 --> 00:00:41.919
If it wasn't right, they aborted it because it wasn't what they had ordered.

00:00:41.920 --> 00:00:47.919
I'm afraid, Andrew, that I don't see any bright lines. Once you go down this path, there won't be any bright lines.

00:00:47.920 --> 00:00:52.459
And then once we genetically modify everybody into perfection, we'll all be exactly the same.

00:00:52.460 --> 00:00:57.473
It's the same spirit that was behind Hitler. The same thinking that Hitler had—it's sickening.

00:00:57.474 --> 00:01:06.668
This should be illegal. We're all fearfully and wonderfully made by the Father. The Lord showed me this and it was very disturbing.

00:01:06.669 --> 00:01:16.546
He showed me surrogate mothers—mothers that did not want to carry a baby but would pay somebody else to do it.

00:01:16.547 --> 00:01:30.079
That would become something that people don't do anymore. I saw lab-tube babies that would be created with AI technology.

00:01:30.080 --> 00:01:37.302
You take the egg and the seed—the sperm—and you make a baby in a lab-tube.

00:01:37.303 --> 00:01:47.072
They would grow it in an incubator. It was like a real womb, a surrogate that didn't have to be human.

00:01:47.073 --> 00:02:02.234
It was a tube in a lab; it wasn't that big. And instead of having a surrogate woman, it was a surrogate tube.

00:02:02.235 --> 00:02:18.159
And they grew the baby to what you had specifically wanted: hair color, eye color, like a Build-a-Bear. It was build-a-baby.

00:02:18.160 --> 00:02:27.215
And they could have the gender they wanted, the hair color, the structure of the body; everything was in design.

00:02:27.216 --> 00:02:40.976
And if it wasn't right, they aborted it because it wasn't what they had ordered, like an AI order.

00:02:40.977 --> 00:02:54.795
This is what we want at the lab. And they created it with genetic modification of human life in a tube. And in certain countries, they made it legal.

00:02:54.796 --> 00:03:03.359
And you did not have to have a surrogate woman anymore to carry your baby for you because the celebrities—these people were into their looks.

00:03:03.360 --> 00:03:15.437
Big-money people were into their looks, and they didn't want to pay for a surrogate because you'd have to worry about what they're eating, what they're drinking, or who they are, or if they're weird.

00:03:15.438 --> 00:03:27.734
They said, "Well, we'll just let the lab do it."They paid mega money for what they specifically wanted for a build-a-child.

00:03:27.735 --> 00:03:40.597
And it was very disturbing. So, I saw the child be born. It was ready to hatch out of this womb thing with bubbles bubbling all around it, keeping the baby alive.

00:03:40.598 --> 00:03:53.221
It was AI technology beyond anything you can comprehend, taking the egg from the woman and the seed from the man and creating a child with your DNA.

00:03:53.222 --> 00:04:01.598
But there was no—and this is what I thought was interesting—I saw the baby and there was no connection.

00:04:01.599 --> 00:04:26.799
What I could see in the face was there was no real connection like when a mother carries a child normally; there's a connection and a bond that is created with the human that is only done by God.

00:04:26.800 --> 00:04:40.851
And when this is not made there, it was almost like looking at a child with autism where the lights are on, but no one's home.

00:04:40.852 --> 00:04:48.020
I don't mean that disrespectfully, but I'm trying to describe it.

00:04:48.021 --> 00:04:55.839
This is what these children looked like in their eyes; there was just this disconnect.

00:04:55.840 --> 00:05:03.198
But I saw this thing coming. Now, I don't know how this would happen. It seems so far out there.

00:05:03.199 --> 00:05:13.634
But the Lord told me to warn you that this is coming: lab-grown children, lab-grown life.

00:05:13.635 --> 00:05:21.663
Then I saw them in labs, and they were doing genetic code in Japan and China and some other places.

00:05:21.664 --> 00:05:31.617
I don't know if the United States would come right out and do this very fast, but I saw foreign countries have no restraints.

00:05:31.618 --> 00:05:53.688
I saw lab-grown babies again. And they were making something that looked like a superhuman—what they thought was a perfect child.

00:05:53.689 --> 00:06:15.839
They were trying to be like Hitler with ethnic cleansing. This is what they will eliminate by making a superhuman race without any kind of flaws through an artificial womb.

00:06:15.840 --> 00:06:44.638
An artificial womb that looked the size of a toilet bowl. As it was growing and developing, if it wasn't what they wanted, they just aborted it—build-a-baby.

00:06:44.639 --> 00:06:56.154
And I said that yesterday; I was hearing a celebrity and many of you got her name right, which I thought was interesting.

00:06:56.154 --> 00:07:03.554
My son told me who you all were saying in the chat and there were so many people saying the exact same person.

00:07:03.555 --> 00:07:16.954
I heard her talking and I will never say it on here, and I encourage you all not to either, but they were saying it right.

00:07:16.955 --> 00:07:32.248
I heard the celebrity talking and they were saying this is convenient so as not to put stress on the woman's body because it's too much for their organs.

00:07:32.249 --> 00:07:53.515
This is more convenient so that we can multiply our bloodlines to make sure that name is sustained in the earth.

00:07:53.516 --> 00:08:03.954
You want to make sure you have strong men to take on that name. Some names mean more than others in their opinion.

00:08:03.954 --> 00:08:18.621
So you raise up a bunch of these celebrity names and males to take on that name of that celebrity or royalty.

00:08:18.622 --> 00:08:25.088
But in a superhuman, beautiful eyes—this is guaranteed, ma'am.

00:08:25.089 --> 00:08:35.973
You put this in there and they're never going to have cancer; we'll be able to take that genetic out of there. And it was so sickening what I was watching happening.

00:08:35.974 --> 00:08:57.575
But the Lord said, "This is closer than you realize."When I was in there looking at the vision, I heard the voice of the Lord and he said, "This is closer than you realize."And then I saw babies in labs in amniotic fluid with bubbling and a light behind it.

00:08:57.576 --> 00:09:10.728
It looked like a hot light keeping this baby warm, like something in a sci-fi movie.

00:09:10.729 --> 00:09:22.108
What you could see wasn't fully developed yet. I could see the nose and the head and how it separates from the egg and the sperm.

00:09:22.109 --> 00:09:26.239
Life without a mother. And I saw they were doing it; it was successful.

00:09:26.240 --> 00:09:46.638
It was alive in a cylinder tube, suspended in this amniotic fluid stuff and real-life bubbles that were moving around this human life.

00:09:46.639 --> 00:09:52.438
I could see the fluids and it looked like the amniotic fluid had a yellow tint.

00:09:52.439 --> 00:10:07.120
It looked like a shade of urine, but it looked thick like jelly.

00:10:07.121 --> 00:10:13.759
The baby was suspended in this tube and it was being grown in a lab.

00:10:13.760 --> 00:10:24.920
And I could actually see an umbilical cord, some kind of cord attached to this fetus, to this baby.

